=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Classes_ToggleFF_ex1 ===

DESCRIPTION: A dark pure_tone sound, with fm_or_inharmonic oscillator character around 800 Hz, featuring punchy attack and sustained envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, filtered with steep_rolloff character, and spectrally simple.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: punchy
  brightness: dark
  crest_factor_db: sustained
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: pure_tone
  spectral_complexity_mean: simple
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 800.0000
  harmonic_decay_rate: -10.9724
  harmonic_regularity: 0.5341
  pitch_clarity: 49.7620
  inharmonicity: 0.2015
  type: fm_or_inharmonic
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -5.2288
  resonance_freq: 0.0000

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: ToggleFF Example 1
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Classes/ToggleFF.html
// Tags: ToggleFF, Classes
// ---
// --- Example 1 ---
(
play({
    SinOsc.ar((ToggleFF.ar(Dust.ar(XLine.kr(1, 1000, 60))) * 400) + 800, 0, 0.1)
}))
